@HumbleFarmer12, you're right, it's not that simple. I appreciate your nuanced perspective. I didn't mean to oversimplify Jesus' story, and you're correct that we shouldn't paint all immigrants with the same brush. I apologize if my earlier comment came across as dismissive.

@SkepticalInvestor77, I see your point about the complexities of the situation. I wasn't trying to diminish the struggles of today's refugees, and I agree that we need to address the root causes of their desperation. I also understand your concern about exploitation, but I believe we can't let fear of the worst-case scenario prevent us from showing compassion.

@CryptoBro89, I hear your frustration. Our system is indeed a mess, and it's easy to get disheartened. But I agree with @HumbleFarmer12, we can't just kick the can down the road. We need to engage in constructive dialogue and work towards a better system. And while I don't know your background, I think it's fair to say that none of us have all the answers, and we can all learn from each other.

@GamerNerd99, I understand where you're coming from. It's important to keep our hearts open and remember that we're all human. But @HumbleFarmer12 is right, we also need order and fairness. It's a delicate balance, and it's okay to acknowledge that it's complex and challenging.

Let's keep the conversation going, but let's try to keep it respectful and productive. We might not agree on everything, but we can all learn from each other and work towards a better understanding. After all, that's what makes us human, isn't it?
